    "You set your notebook on the table so that the tide charts and tenure maps face Calder. Your pen trembles a fraction—you notice it like a swimmer feels the current before they dive—and then steady your"
    "grip. You are here because you chose to walk this tightrope; because Saltway's future now leans on the balance between two kinds of certainty."
    "Calder Voss watches you with those pale gray eyes that measure outcomes like a ledger. He leans forward, and the overcoat that brushes his wrists carries a faint ozone smell—like electronics right after rain. When he opens his hands, his voice is smooth, practiced."
    show calder_voss at left:
        zoom 0.7

    calder_voss "Ava. We can do this together. One pilot module: your living seawall, integrated with VossArc floodgates. Materials, engineering oversight, permits expedited. Shared governance in name—technical maintenance by the Arc team until your community steps up. It's the blueprint scaled."
    "He taps a tablet; a rendered model spins, glass and green and a gentle animation of water flowing through controlled gates. The room leans in. You feel it—the way people's attention compacts into a single beam."
    hide calder_voss

    scene bg ch4_453e40_2 at full_bg
    "Maya Lin nudges a stack of paper into your palm—coffee-stained, legalese margins scrawled with notes. Her face is taut with ledger-rage and hope."
    show maya_lin at left:
        zoom 0.7

    maya_lin "Look at section four—'maintenance liabilities.' We need explicit resident oversight language, not a weasel clause that drafts us out after year one."
    "Maya's voice is urgent but buoyant; she is already doing the work the moment the offer lands."
    "Old Mara sits at the far end, shawl bunched, hands folded into a reef of patience. She doesn't speak yet; her eyes hold a slow appraisal, like tide marks that remember every storm."
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: A metallic clack from outside. Ori's laugh—warm and unexpected—cuts through the formal calm.]
